node.title: Victoria records 1,069 new local COVID-19 cases and 10 deaths
node.alt: Shoppers both seated and walking in a Melbourne arcade with a Christmas tree in the background.
node.description: There are now 15,607 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 376 people have died during the state's current Delta outbreak.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 1,069\u00a0new local COVID-19 cases and 10\u00a0deaths.", "There are now 15,607\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 376\u00a0people have died during the state's current Delta outbreak.", "There are 579\u00a0people in hospital with COVID-19, of whom 90\u00a0are in intensive care and 55\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "The new cases were detected from 47,794\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There were 11,269\u00a0doses of vaccine given at state-run sites yesterday, and more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "More to come.", "", "
How to take a rapid antigen test
